A REST API is a web interface that lets clients manipulate resources by using standard HTTP verbs (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) on well‑structured URLs. It’s stateless, meaning each request contains all the information needed, and it often exchanges data in lightweight formats like JSON. Because it follows uniform resource identification and resource‑centric design, REST APIs are easy to understand, scale, and integrate across different platforms.
